00:33:21,780 --> 00:33:24,160
Okay. Moving on.

604
00:33:24,590 --> 00:33:25,930
Oh, hi. 
Sorry. I'll come back.

605
00:33:25,931 --> 00:33:28,510
No, no, hey. Come here.

606
00:33:28,940 --> 00:33:30,130
Rounds are over.

607
00:33:30,131 --> 00:33:32,510
All right. Everyone get some sleep.

608
00:33:33,820 --> 00:33:36,150
We had a snake in the O.R. last night.

609
00:33:36,840 --> 00:33:38,930
Snakes in the operating room?

610
00:33:39,010 --> 00:33:40,190
That's ridiculous.

611
00:33:40,191 --> 00:33:42,999
Yeah? Graham. Get the snake.

612
00:33:43,000 --> 00:33:44,050
Yes, sir.

613
00:33:44,560 --> 00:33:46,250
And while he's getting the snake,

614
00:33:46,940 --> 00:33:49,710
I want to talk about the dust. 
Dust? I--

615
00:33:54,570 --> 00:33:56,110
Hey, I was, um, I was wondering

616
00:33:56,120 --> 00:33:58,270
if you wouldn't mind running a test for me.

617
00:33:58,640 --> 00:34:00,709
The thing is, I don't have any paperwork.

618
00:34:00,710 --> 00:34:03,060
Oh, that's no problem, doc.
What do you need?

619
00:34:03,310 --> 00:34:05,370
Just a basic pregnancy panel.

620
00:34:05,990 --> 00:34:07,160
It's for a friend.

621
00:34:07,710 --> 00:34:10,460
She's military and doesn't
want to get sent home, so--

622
00:34:10,710 --> 00:34:11,860
Rest your mind, doc.

623
00:34:11,861 --> 00:34:14,389
Nothing from here ever
goes outside the Role 3

624
00:34:14,390 --> 00:34:15,570
unless you say.

625
00:34:18,620 --> 00:34:20,190
So you're feeling better?

626
00:34:20,560 --> 00:34:22,360
They won't give me a card,
but your mom called.

627
00:34:22,361 --> 00:34:23,650
I think he's good to go to iso.

628
00:34:23,651 --> 00:34:24,600
Want to double-check?

629
00:34:24,601 --> 00:34:26,590
No, if you're happy, I'm happy.

630
00:34:26,820 --> 00:34:28,180
All right. Ready?

631
00:34:34,950 --> 00:34:37,270
I'd say a real nice shaving cream.

632
00:34:39,540 --> 00:34:40,620
You the surgeon?

633
00:34:43,050 --> 00:34:45,170
Who wants to know? Dr. Trang?

634
00:34:45,580 --> 00:34:46,790
Yeah. 
Dr. Trang?

635
00:34:48,100 --> 00:34:50,170
Who are you, and where are the M.P.s?

636
00:34:50,220 --> 00:34:53,620
We took over. When can he be moved?

637
00:34:53,850 --> 00:34:55,170
When he's well enough.

638
00:34:55,240 --> 00:34:56,760
When will that be, miss?

639
00:34:57,890 --> 00:35:00,069
It's Doctor or Major, not miss,

640
00:35:00,070 --> 00:35:02,170
and he's well enough when I say so.

641
00:35:02,220 --> 00:35:03,710
Rebecca, you got a sec?

642
00:35:04,630 --> 00:35:06,040
Yeah, I'll be right there.

643
00:35:07,570 --> 00:35:08,920
Any more questions?

644
00:35:09,440 --> 00:35:10,460
No?

645
00:35:10,800 --> 00:35:12,040
Then excuse me.

646
00:35:18,260 --> 00:35:20,740
This is Dr. Gordon.
She's the one who saved your life.

647
00:35:20,790 --> 00:35:23,079
Uh, no, it wasn't me. I just assisted.

648
00:35:23,080 --> 00:35:25,279
Thank him.
Well, what can I say, except, uh--

649
00:35:25,280 --> 00:35:26,850
Don't look at me. It was her.

650
00:35:26,900 --> 00:35:29,779
I just--I just--I'm so-- Dr. Trang
was your trauma team leader.

651
00:35:29,780 --> 00:35:32,460
So if you want to thank
somebody, thank him. Thank her.

652
00:35:33,330 --> 00:35:36,430
Well, uh, both of you, thank you.
I'm--I'm really--

653
00:35:36,910 --> 00:35:39,339
Conrad! 
Oh, man. What's wrong?

654
00:35:39,340 --> 00:35:40,400
No, back up.

655
00:35:41,330 --> 00:35:43,249
I need Diazepam, 5 plus 5 I.M.,

656
00:35:43,250 --> 00:35:45,960
then 1 gram phytoin over 20 minutes.

657
00:35:50,030 --> 00:35:51,620
How close was he to the explosion?

658
00:35:51,860 --> 00:35:53,310
Next to me, but he wasn't hurt.

659
00:35:53,311 --> 00:35:56,300
Was he unconscious at any point?
Only for a minute.

660
00:35:58,690 --> 00:35:59,740
What's going on?

661
00:36:02,740 --> 00:36:05,389
Okay, we got blood in the belly, and lots.

662
00:36:05,390 --> 00:36:07,819
Splenic rupture. We've got a blown pupil.

663
00:36:07,820 --> 00:36:09,130
We need Dr. Hill.

664
00:36:09,570 --> 00:36:11,120
All right, he needs a C.T. scan right now. 
Call Dr. Hill!

665
00:36:11,121 --> 00:36:13,590
We gotta get him on a gurney.
What's happening?

666
00:36:14,080 --> 00:36:15,360
He's been bleeding internally.

667
00:36:15,361 --> 00:36:18,940
But he was fine. He was fine.

668
00:36:37,160 --> 00:36:38,630
More F.F.P.

669
00:36:43,830 --> 00:36:45,460
Can we pull the curtain, please?

670
00:36:49,440 --> 00:36:51,740
Cardiac arrest. Starting C.P.R.

671
00:36:52,360 --> 00:36:54,230
One one thousand. Two one thousand.

672
00:36:54,240 --> 00:36:56,140
Three one thousand. Four one thousand.

673
00:36:56,141 --> 00:36:59,660
Five one thousand. Six one thousand.
Seven one thousand--

674
00:36:59,800 --> 00:37:02,140
I don't think this brain
damage is survivable.

675
00:37:02,450 --> 00:37:05,820
He's not clotting at all either.
O-2 sat 93% and falling.

676
00:37:06,320 --> 00:37:08,580
Does anyone think there's
anything else we can do?

677
00:37:09,310 --> 00:37:11,519
17 one thousand. 18 one thousand.

678
00:37:11,520 --> 00:37:13,869
19 one thousand. 20 one thousand.

679
00:37:13,870 --> 00:37:14,620
21 one thousand.

680
00:37:14,621 --> 00:37:16,550
Okay. 22 one thousand. 23 one thousand.

681
00:37:16,551 --> 00:37:18,250
Stop C.P.R. 24--

682
00:37:21,820 --> 00:37:24,810
17 local time, Kandahar.

683
00:37:25,280 --> 00:37:26,510
Let's take a moment.

684
00:37:44,010 --> 00:37:45,900
But I was the one that was hurt.

685
00:37:46,400 --> 00:37:48,310
Okay? 
Not him. He was fine.

686
00:37:48,570 --> 00:37:50,169
He wasn't, I'm sorry to say.

687
00:37:50,170 --> 00:37:51,870
He thought he was, but he wasn't.

688
00:37:52,820 --> 00:37:54,930
Maybe if we had gotten to him sooner--

689
00:37:55,870 --> 00:37:56,880
I don't know.

690
00:37:57,780 --> 00:37:58,970
We're very sorry.

691
00:38:00,620 --> 00:38:02,420
I'm sure you did everything you could.

692
00:38:18,810 --> 00:38:19,930
What the hell?

693
00:38:25,500 --> 00:38:26,670
Attention!

694
00:38:28,100 --> 00:38:30,270
Hut. Salute.

695
00:38:46,220 --> 00:38:46,770
Colonel--

696
00:38:46,771 --> 00:38:48,779
The Taliban prisoner's gone missing.
I heard.

697
00:38:48,780 --> 00:38:51,850
No, he hasn't gone missing. He was taken.

698
00:38:52,510 --> 00:38:53,780
Why aren't you pissed off?

699
00:38:53,781 --> 00:38:55,880
I'm pissed off for the
same reason you are--

700
00:38:56,870 --> 00:38:58,560
that we lost that young soldier.

701
00:38:59,970 --> 00:39:02,020
I take it personally when we lose one.

702
00:39:03,760 --> 00:39:05,080
I see that you do, too.

703
00:39:05,490 --> 00:39:06,090
But what about--

704
00:39:06,091 --> 00:39:07,770
That's my problem, not yours.

705
00:39:08,560 --> 00:39:09,610
I'm on it.

706
00:39:13,270 --> 00:39:14,380
Get some sleep.

707
00:39:15,140 --> 00:39:15,940
That's an order.

708
00:39:15,950 --> 00:39:16,950
Yes, sir.

709
00:39:20,610 --> 00:39:21,590
Hey.

710
00:39:21,620 --> 00:39:24,980
I have completely lost track.
How long has it been?

711
00:39:25,240 --> 00:39:26,080
Since we've been here?

712
00:39:26,081 --> 00:39:27,100
Yeah.

713
00:39:27,300 --> 00:39:30,400
Let's see, it was night,
then day, then night--

714
00:39:31,170 --> 00:39:32,820
Mm-hmm. I don't know. I've lost track, too.

715
00:39:33,040 --> 00:39:36,200
Well, finally, we get to sleep.

716
00:39:37,020 --> 00:39:38,500
Actually, there's one more thing.

717
00:39:39,150 --> 00:39:40,290
You're kidding me.

718
00:39:40,291 --> 00:39:41,380
No.

719
00:39:42,770 --> 00:39:43,700
I don't really know what to do

720
00:39:43,710 --> 00:39:46,670
except just to hand it to you.

721
00:39:49,660 --> 00:39:51,100
The lab guy gave this to you?

722
00:39:51,110 --> 00:39:52,700
To give to you, yes.

723
00:39:53,090 --> 00:39:55,340
Look, he was trying to get your attention,

724
00:39:55,430 --> 00:39:57,640
but you were so focused
on finding the Colonel--

725
00:39:58,030 --> 00:40:00,120
Anyway, he didn't mean anything by it,

726
00:40:00,460 --> 00:40:02,070
you know, since it was for your friend.

727
00:40:18,280 --> 00:40:20,120
You read it, naturally.

728
00:40:20,880 --> 00:40:23,120
It wasn't exactly in a sealed envelope.

729
00:40:27,170 --> 00:40:30,080
Well, you're the diagnostician.

730
00:40:30,420 --> 00:40:32,479
And as I'm sure you've already figured out,

731
00:40:32,480 --> 00:40:34,979
I thought that I might be pregnant,

732
00:40:34,980 --> 00:40:37,180
and according to this, I am not.

733
00:40:38,040 --> 00:40:40,490
I have never missed my period.

734
00:40:44,710 --> 00:40:47,750
Okay, it could be one of
a few things or nothing.

735
00:40:48,540 --> 00:40:50,220
A blood test will tell us.

736
00:40:50,780 --> 00:40:52,470
Can you stay awake for another half-hour?

737
00:40:53,340 --> 00:40:56,110
Honestly? No.

738
00:40:58,460 --> 00:41:00,339
This is what I was worried about.

739
00:41:00,340 --> 00:41:02,820
If it is anything else, I can wait.

740
00:41:03,580 --> 00:41:06,850
The only thing that I care
about right now is sleep.

741
00:41:06,860 --> 00:41:07,850
Yeah.

742
00:41:16,680 --> 00:41:17,760
There!

743
00:41:23,110 --> 00:41:25,670
Done! Over and out.

744
00:41:26,880 --> 00:41:28,530
Remind me never to get on your wrong side.

745
00:41:28,531 --> 00:41:31,089
Oh, don't worry. I will. Night.

746
00:41:31,090 --> 00:41:32,100
Night.

747
00:41:33,440 --> 00:41:34,250
9-1-1.

748
00:41:34,260 --> 00:41:36,700
Oh, for the love of God!

749
00:41:41,500 --> 00:41:42,280
Hurry up! Hurry up!

750
00:41:42,281 --> 00:41:45,050
We have five ambulances at the main gate!

751
00:41:53,340 --> 00:41:54,460
You were right.

752
00:41:54,930 --> 00:41:56,680
Nothing prepared me for this place.

